'''Hamilton Boyle, 6th Earl of Cork and 6th Earl of Orrery''' (3 February 1729 &ndash; 17 January 1764) was the son of [[John Boyle, 5th Earl of Cork]] and Henrietta Douglas.  He inherited the titles of 6th Earl of Cork and Orrery and 3rd Baron Boyle of Marston from his father in 1762.

He served in the [[Parliament of Great Britain]] as [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Warwick (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwick]] between 1751 and 1762, and represented [[Charleville (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Charleville]] in the [[Irish House of Commons]] between 1759 and 1760.<ref> {{cite web|url = http://www.ancestryireland.com/family-records/biographies-of-the-members-of-the-irish-parliament/?search1=Hamilton&search2=Boyle&search3=&submit=Search|title= Biographies of Members of the Irish Parliament 1692-1800| publisher= Ulster Historical Foundation|accessdate = 21 June 2014}} </ref>  He was unmarried and was succeeded by his brother.

